
<p>Sociobiologist Edward O. Wilson, back in 2009:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>The real problem of humanity is the following: we have paleolithic
emotions; medieval institutions; and god-like technology.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>A related adage I heard, and internalized, recently: “We’re not thinking creatures who feel; we’re feeling creatures who think.” (<a href="https://kottke.org/25/11/0047871-edward-o-wilson-in-2009">Via Jason Kottke</a>.)</p>

